dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.swcomponenttemplate.datatype.dataprototypes

Interface IVariableDataPrototype

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAutosarDataPrototype, IEntity, IIdentifiable, IReferrable

    public interface IVariableDataPrototype
extends IEntity, IAutosarDataPrototype
    IVariableDataPrototype: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    A VariableDataPrototype is used to contain values in an ECU application. This means that most likely a VariableDataPrototype allocates "static" memory on the ECU. In some cases optimization strategies might lead to a situation where the memory allocation can be avoided. In particular, the value of a VariableDataPrototype is likely to change as the ECU on which it is used executes.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!
